This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques applied to political campaign text. The focus is on speech act classification, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of contextualized word representations, which is a popular technique in natural language processing and falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of semi-supervised learning, which is a common technique in machine learning and falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of task dependencies, which is a common technique in machine learning and falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the use of speaker meta-data, which falls under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY).
